reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars A Space-Saving Marvel for Compact Kitchens
reviews.reviewText: The MOUKABAL Over The Sink Dish Drying Rack has proven to be a game-changer in my compact kitchen, where space is a precious commodity. This adjustable and multifunctional dish drying rack has not only maximized my counter space but has also brought a new level of efficiency to my daily kitchen routine.One of the standout features of this rack is its adjustability. With a length range of 23.6"-34.6", it fits snugly over my sink, making efficient use of the space. The ability to extend or retract the rack allows me to customize it to my specific needs, ensuring a perfect fit even in kitchens with limited counter space.As someone with upper cabinets limiting the space on the left and right, the MOUKABAL Over The Sink Dish Drying Rack has provided a smart and practical solution. The over-the-sink design allows for efficient water drainage directly into the sink, eliminating the need for a separate drying mat or tray.The rack's multifunctionality is another highlight. The adjustable baskets can be moved around to accommodate various kitchen items, from plates and utensils to cutting boards and pans. This flexibility not only adds convenience but also enhances the overall organization of the drying process.The construction of the rack is sturdy and durable, thanks to its metal framework. The black finish adds a sleek and modern touch to my kitchen decor. Installation was straightforward, and the rack feels secure and stable over the sink.In terms of usability, the MOUKABAL Over The Sink Dish Drying Rack has streamlined my kitchen chores. The convenience of having all washed items in one central location, coupled with the efficient drainage, has made dish drying more organized and less time-consuming.Overall, I highly recommend the MOUKABAL Over The Sink Dish Drying Rack to anyone facing space constraints in their kitchen. Its adjustable design, space-saving features, and multifunctionality make it a valuable addition for those seeking an efficient and organized solution to dish drying.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Measure carefully, and be careful with heavier dishes
reviews.reviewText: Product sides and back bars seems pretty strong. The racks, and especially the wire-only ones, a bit on the lightweight side, so don't put heavier items in them, for sure. We have some hefty dinner plates / bowls, and I would not put more than 4 to 6 on this rack. For thinner / lighter-weight plates, especially plastic ones, this should be fine.The black finish is nice - hopefully it holds up over time with repeated water contact. The instructions are a bit lacking in places, as some of the descriptions do not fully detail what the picture shows, so you do need to use a bit of thought to get it together by both reading *and* fully studying the diagrams for each step.One thing that is not really done well is how to handle adjusting the width. The inner "middle" bar is just set in each side with no "stop" unless you lock one side first. If you are going at one of the wider settings, be sure to lock one side down first, and then move the other side to adjust rack width.Be sure to measure carefully, and not just the width, but also the height of your faucet and anything else on the back of your sink.
